jobInfo.postDescription:
RESPONSIBILITIES (Key accountabilities and responsibilities)

• Prior to commencing software tasks, ensure that a clear schedule has been agreed with Software Engineering Manager and Software Team Leader. 
在开发工作之前，与技术工程经理和组长沟通达成清晰的工作流程；
• Ensure both software enhancements and corrections are implemented following the agreed software development process. Work on complex technical tasks with high expectations of quality and productivity.
始终按照公司的开发流程工作，以保证文档和软件产品的质量。高质量、高产量地完成比较复杂的开发任务；
• Notify the Software Engineering Manager and Software Team Leader immediately of risks or significant issues that could affect the ability to meet scheduled dates.
在开发流程中及时汇报工作进程。在过程中如果预见可能存在重大影响的风险因素，第一时间与团队成员、组长以及部门经理沟通；
• Share with Software Team Leader and the rest of the software team any useful information that could aid the efficiency of the team. Proactively recommend software changes to improve efficiency, reliability and stability. Contribute to the development and enhancement of software engineering processes and tools. 
主动分享对开发工作有用的技术信息以及创新技术方案，为整个技术工程部门开发流程、工具以及团队合作提供支持；
• Provide support to the System Engineering, Integration and Verification & Validation teams and other teams when necessary.
对其他技术工程部门提供必要的支持，包括系统工程，集成，测试组；
• Mentor and coach assigned team members when requested. Be recognised within the team as expert for assigned software components. 
在日常工作中辅导软件开发工程师，能够在团队中建立自己的专家权威，并分享自己的专家知识和经验；
• When requested, perform induction training and detailed technical training for software components where expertise has been established. Assist in interviews of new software engineers, when required.
如有需要，为团队提供软件开发相关的技术培训；参与软件开发工程师的面试工作。

QUALIFICATION

• Bachelor's Degree (or higher) in Computer Science or other relevant majors.
计算机科学或相关专业的本科及以上学历。

• 2 year experience of software development in a business environment.
2年软件开发工作经验：
* Experience as a major contributor in development of one or more complex systems.
作为主要参与者，有过一个或多个大型复杂项目的项目经验；
* Proficient in C, C++ and ADA.
熟练使用C, C++, ADA语言开发；
*Proficient in UNIX/Linux Ope
